JOHANNESBURG - Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF) leader Julius Malema visited Winnie Madikizela-Mandela's home in Soweto on Tuesday afternoon. The EFF said in a statement Malema will pay his respect to Madikizela-Mandela on behalf of his party. Malema: We are here today to say a spear has fallen and we are here to pick up that spear and continue the struggle for emancipation. READ: Rights warrior Mama Winnie honoured On Monday, the party described Madikizela-Mandela as a warrior. EFF Deputy President Floyd Shivambu said she anchored key political campaigns over the years, including the 1976 student uprising. #WinnieMandela Around 300 @EFFSouthAfrica members have begun marching towards the house pic.twitter.com/4mQX4xpdjy eNCA